                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43771",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've attached a fix for this issue.  It modifies Zend_Oauth_Config to add a 'realm' attribute, and modifies Zend_Oauth_Client:250 to add realm to the toHeader() call as outlined in reporter's post. \r\n\r\nI haven't had much experience yet with using Zend_Oauth, so i'm not entirely certain this is the best way to add the ability to configure the realm.  Comments?",
